public enum AuthoringDirectiveType
extends java.lang.Enum<AuthoringDirectiveType>

The different types of Authoring Directives that can be use to control the behavior of the Authoring interface after an AuthoringAction has been executed.

Since:
v8.0

Enum Constant Summary
CLOSE
          When the extension returns a "Close" directive, the authoring interface will close the form.
CONTINUE
          When the extension returns a "Continue" directive, the authoring interface will reload the form.
EDIT_MODE
          When the extension returns a "Edit Mode" directive, the authoring interface will open the edit mode form.
OPEN_DOCUMENT
          When the extension returns a "Open Document" directive, the authoring interface will open the specified target document.
READ_MODE
          When the extension returns a "Read Mode" directive, the authoring interface will open the read mode form.
